article.description: Courtney Moses scored 14 points to lead Purdue to a 73-36 victory over IPFW on Thursday night.
article.headline: Courtney Moses scores 14 to lead Purdue to easy victory
article.linkText: Moses scores 14 to lead Purdue to easy victory
article.story:
WEST LAFAYETTE, Ind. --  Courtney Moses scored 14 points to lead Purdue (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) to a 73-36 victory over IPFW on Thursday night.

Sam Ostarello added 13 points and eight rebounds, Brittany Rayburn had 11 points and four assists, and Antionette Howard added 10 points and nine rebounds for the Boilermakers (10-3) in their final nonconference game.

Stephanie Rosado scored nine points to lead IPFW (4-8).

The Mastodons shot 23 percent from the field and made just 5 of 23 3-pointers, while committing 22 turnovers.

Purdue shot 46 percent from the field and outrebounded IPFW 40-32.

The Boilermakers open Big Ten play on Dec. 30 at home against Minnesota.
